<TR>… he [viz.\ the guru] should proclaim (<skt>udgīrya</skt>) the mantra and the traditional teaching (<skt>saṃpradāyam</skt>) that have been passed down to him through the lineage of his gurus and he should give [the mantra and sampradāya] into his cupped hands, from his own cupped hands, which should be full of flowers.</TR>

[4.49]
